Task 5: Personal Loan Acceptance Prediction
Predicting Customer Response to Bank Marketing Campaigns
Project Overview
This project focuses on predicting which customers are likely to accept a personal loan offer (term deposit) based on their demographic and financial profiles. By analyzing factors such as age, job, and marital status, we help the bank identify high-potential leads for their marketing campaigns.

The project was developed using Python in Google Colab and implements a classification model to distinguish between customers who accept or decline the offer.

Objective
The main objective of this project is to:

Perform basic data exploration on key customer features

Understand the impact of age, job, and marital status on loan acceptance

Train a machine learning classifier (Logistic Regression/Decision Tree)

Identify specific customer groups with the highest likelihood of acceptance

Evaluate the model using classification metrics

Dataset
Dataset used: Bank Marketing Dataset (UCI Machine Learning Repository)

Dataset Link: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/janiobachmann/bank-marketing-dataset

File used: * bank.csv (or bank-full.csv)

