Data Preprocessing
Missing Values: The dataset was checked for null entries (usually clean in UCI versions).

Encoding: Categorical variables like 'job', 'marital', and 'education' were converted into numerical format using Label Encoding to make them compatible with the machine learning model.

Exploratory Data Analysis
Visualizations were created to satisfy the task requirements:

Age Distribution: Identifying the primary age groups of bank customers.

Job Distribution: A count plot showing the variety of professions represented.

Marital Status: Analyzing the marital background of the customer base.

Success by Category: Bar charts showing acceptance rates across different demographics.

Model Evaluation
The model performance was evaluated using:

Accuracy Score

Confusion Matrix

Classification Report (Precision, Recall, F1-Score)

Model Accuracy
Accuracy Achieved: [INSERT YOUR ACCURACY HERE, e.g., 89.2%]

Results & Insights
Target Demographics: Middle-aged customers and specific job categories (like 'technician' or 'management') showed higher interest in loan offers.

Behavioral Patterns: Customers with longer contact durations during the campaign were significantly more likely to accept.

Marital Influence: Married individuals formed the largest group of respondents.

How to Run the Project
Open the notebook in Google Colab.

Upload the bank.csv dataset file.

Run all cells sequentially.

Review the visualizations and the final classification report.

